latestComments/4/text:
Extremely disappointed with my @motorola  7kg front load washing machine. Bought it on 11th August 2024, and within just 1 month, it broke down. The “comprehensive” warranty only covers the motor and drum, while other parts like the door lock cost ₹2300 to replace! #FalsePromises

I called #Motorola customer care, and they redirected me to #Ekart, where I had to mention the brand, product, and complaint all over again—basically the same info I had already provided by pressing buttons through the Motorola customer care system! #Frustrating

Called #Flipkart on 15th October, and the customer service agent assured me I wouldn’t have to pay for parts. But when the technician came on 17th October, I was told I’d have to pay for the door lock. To make matters worse, my clothes were stuck inside the machine for an entire day, and when the technician finally arrived, they were completely ruined. #TerribleExperience

The technician said the door lock needed replacing, but later changed his diagnosis to the PCB being burnt out, which was luckily covered under warranty. How can a company like #Motorola have such poor service and unreliable products? Truly disappointed!

I would NOT recommend this washing machine to anyone. Save yourself the trouble and get a better brand.

#WorstExperience #MotoFail #FlipkartCustomerService #FrustratedCustomer #PoorService
